name: Pura Jagatnatha Jembrana
address: Jl. Sudirman, Dauhwaru, Kec. Negara, Kabupaten Jembrana, Bali 82218, Indonesia
review 1: An excellent worship place beautifully arranged almost perfect! Entering the tropical garden on the main entrance of the Pura is like entering a little paradise. Lotus pond with red brigde in the middle and many statues of Balinese dancers give a strong taste of the local culture. Two huge metal doors are definitely a statement of an important place to welcome the visitors before entering the main place of worship itself. A huge amphiteatre is placed  between the garden and the Pura for the occasional performance. And finally two Garuda statues welcome the worshipers to enter the grand Pura Jagathnata. A huge wooden carved door in the middle entrance and two smaller sizes of bright red carved wooden on both sides showing the granduer of the place. A neatly maintance green yard decorated with frangipanis tree makes the place even more special. Three open classical Balinese buildings to store the balinese musical intruments placed next to the Pura. The magical atmosphere is really present strongly here. Recomended for the Balinese culture lovers.
review 2: Beautiful, moreover in the night! The place also quiet and has a good atmosphere
review 3: Pretty and very quiet place when we were there...
review 4: I like the gate! But i can't enter the garden
review 5: Beautiful free place, but take sarong.
